            "finding": "95.8% kernel efficiency on first implementation",
            "evidence": "69.83% actual vs 72.88% theoretical maximum",
            "implication": "The row packing approach is near-optimal. Further gains require hardware-level changes such as async prefetch and shared memory tiling."
